==English==
===Etymology===
From the Proto-Indo-European root *'''[[wī-ro-]]''', ''man''; cognate with Latin '''[[vir]]''', ''man'', ''male''
[[Category:Indo-European root *wī-ro-]]

===Prefix===
'''were-'''
# man; prefix most commonly used with animal names to indicate a person who changes shape into that animal.

====Translations====
*Lithuanian: [[-takas]] ''m''; [[-takė]] ''f''

